EXPERIENCE MATTERS









 

Our commercial real estate lending team




ReadyCap Commerical's senior management team has a wealth of experience with a proven track record of leading successful commercial real estate lending operations and staff. Committed to recruiting and retaining the best people, ReadyCap insists on integrity and the bold decisions that drive change. Through deep experience and diversity, the team works to continuously deliver innovative products and efficient processes.
Learn more about our management team:

Anuj Gupta
President

Anuj Gupta has more than 20 years of experience in commercial real estate lending. Prior to assuming the position of President at ReadyCap, Anuj led commercial real estate capital markets and new origination loan pricing for Waterfall Asset Management (“Waterfall”) and ReadyCap, while also playing an integral role in the launch and growth of the bridge and conventional real estate lending platforms. Anuj played a key role in loan originations and acquisitions that eventually sold into $1.5 billion of securitizations that he led. Before joining Waterfall, he co-led the $5 billion U.S. Department of the Treasury sponsored Public-Private Investment Fund Joint Venture between GE Capital and Angelo, Gordon & Co. formed to purchase CMBS and RMBS securities. Anuj was also Head of GE Real Estate’s CMBS group in New York, where he oversaw the origination and securitization of over $3.7 billion of mortgage loans. From 2003 to 2006, Anuj led capital market activities for three GE Capital businesses, particularly launching GE’s small balance real estate originate-to-sell program where he oversaw the build of that securitization program into which over $6 billion of mortgage loans were originated and sold. Anuj was also an Officer at Fannie Mae, a founder of a $300 million per annum start-up specialty finance originator and an analyst in the Mortgage and Asset-Backed Securities Group at Greenwich Capital Markets and NatWest Securities. 
Jackie Schorr
Chief Financial Officer

Jackie Schorr brings over 22 years of financial experience to her elevated role for the ReadyCap organization and its lending divisions. Previously, Schorr served as controller for ReadyCap Lending, the nationally recognized SBA Preferred Lender and subsidiary of ReadyCap Commercial, since its inception in 2014. Prior to joining ReadyCap Lending, Schorr was controller of CIT Small Business Lending, as well as a manager in the Vendor Finance Group for 14 years.

Dominick Scali
Chief Credit Officer - Commercial

Dominick Scali has over 14 years experience in the financial services industry. He has held a handful of leadership positions, and most recently served as a director and head of underwriting and transaction management for Doral Bank. Prior to joining the management team at Doral, Dominick focused on origination, credit and portfolio management as a Vice President at Anglo Irish Bank. Dominick began his career at Citibank as a management associate with a focus on the affordable housing division. Dominick earned a bachelors degree in economics from Columbia University.

Dawnyel Dishman 
Director of Operations 

Dawnyel Dishman has more than 14 years of experience in closing commercial real estate transactions. Prior to joining ReadyCap, Dawnyel spent nearly five years with Fannie Mae, in the Multifamily Loss Mitigation group. Previously, she was the Closing Manager for the Small Balance Originations Platform at Principal Financial Group.



